# Understand the environments GOV.UK Sign in uses

GOV.UK Sign in uses 2 different environments:

* an integration environment, which contains sample users and data for you to test your service’s integration with GOV.UK Sign in
* a production environment, which is the live environment for real users to access and use your service’s integration with GOV.UK Sign in

### Understand and use the integration environment

Before you can use GOV.UK Sign in, you need to build a proof of concept client and explore the end-to-end journey in our integration environment. This will help you understand how to integrate with GOV.UK Sign in, and where it will fit within your service.

1. [Generate a key pair](/generate-a-key/#generate-a-key-pair).
1. [Select supported scopes](/select-supported-scopes/#select-supported-scopes).
1. [Manage your service to use the OpenID Connect provider](/manage-your-service-to-use-OIDC-provider/#manage-your-service-to-use-the-openid-connect-provider).
1. [Integrate with Authorization Code Flow](/integrate-with-code-flow/#integrate-with-authorization-code-flow).

To get started, you’ll need to [generate a key pair](/generate-a-key/#generate-a-key-pair).
